Class AerisCommunicationTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.os.AsyncTask<Void,Void,T>
      • com.hamweather.aeris.communication.CommunicationTask<AerisResponse>
        • com.hamweather.aeris.communication.AerisCommunicationTask
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AerisAbstractTask

    public class AerisCommunicationTask
extends CommunicationTask<AerisResponse>
    Basic communication task for sending messages. Executes the AerisRequest in a background thread. The result of the message is passed back to a Callback interface
    If the message uses a custom end point, the AerisCustomCommunicationTask

      • AerisCommunicationTask

        public AerisCommunicationTask(Context context,
                              AerisRequest request)
        Constructs the communication task with a context to use, and a request. This constructor is intended to be used with CommunicationTask.executeSyncTask() where the task is executed in a non-thread environment and the call will wait for the return object.
        Parameters:
        context - Context to use to check with
        request - Request to use in the thread.
